22 Aug 2008 22:55






5) Souls wouldn't work on the device. Because of either it's abilities, the nature or items of its construction, it's immune to possession.

6) A pile of sand wouldn't because it's not a solid object. The criteria for possession is that the host object must be a mainly solid body, although some liquids can be possessed so long as they're in a container. The host object has to be big enough to accommodate the soul, and the object also must be something affected by human hands. It can't be something random like an odd rock.

7) It either gets jammed in the machine and dissipates, or gets stuck in there until it can be extracted.

8) It could probably modify, combine, alter souls, but since most of the manual was destroyed no one really knows how to do it, and they're a little wary of destroying the device through misuse.

9) It'd go through all the actions, but the there'd be no soul at the end of it. Like trying to wring blood from a stone.

Again, thanks!







